1
00:00:07,041 --> 00:00:08,250
[men grunting]

2
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:16,125
Don't hold back.

3
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:19,875
I am the original <i>Viral Hit</i>.

4
00:00:19,958 --> 00:00:22,708
- [tense music playing]
- [men laughing]

5
00:00:27,250 --> 00:00:29,250
You know what? You're coming with us.

6
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,083
You bitch!

7
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,416
[man 1 grunting]

8
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,000
[man 2 gasping]

9
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:45,458
- [yells] Ah!
- [cracking]

10
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:48,583
[snarls] Ah!

11
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:50,958
[guard] The hell are you doing?

12
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:02,833
BE STRONGER

13
00:01:02,916 --> 00:01:04,333
[Kaho] I had the same key chain.

14
00:01:07,083 --> 00:01:08,250
I guess it's rather childish.

15
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:10,291
No, I don't think so.

16
00:01:10,708 --> 00:01:14,958
It…  was very important to me.

17
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:19,000
- [somber music playing]
- [no audible dialogue]

18
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:25,541
[Kaho] <i>Last year,</i>

19
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:27,875
<i>my mother passed away.</i>

20
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:30,791
And my father remarried.

21
00:01:33,041 --> 00:01:35,416
<i>I'd treasured it for a long time,</i>

22
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,666
<i>but I must have lost it somewhere.</i>

23
00:01:38,708 --> 00:01:41,250
<i>So, I'd been looking for it</i>
<i>all over the place.</i>

24
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,333
[poignant music playing]

25
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:48,166
<i>Then I stumbled upon one just like it.</i>

26
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:07,000
FIGHTING MINDSET
UNLISTED

27
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:11,375
<i>Hello guys! My name is TOU-KEI.</i>

28
00:02:11,458 --> 00:02:14,166
Why don't you come
2and get stronger with me?

29
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,583
Tell me,

30
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:17,625
why did you send me those videos?

31
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:21,291
I saw you being bullied and I was angry.

32
00:02:23,625 --> 00:02:26,625
[boys grunting]

33
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:29,583
- [Hamaken grunts]
- [Shimura whimpering] I'm sorry.

34
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:30,500
[Hamaken] Sorry…

35
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:32,875
- [Kaho] <i>I wanted to help you somehow.</i>
<i>- </i>[dull thud]

36
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:37,583
<i>So I sent you progressive videos</i>
<i>from the same URL.</i>

37
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:40,833
[boys grunting on video]

38
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:42,916
[suspenseful music playing]

39
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:46,166
[Hamaken] <i>Don't you ever mess</i>
<i>with me again, you hear?</i>

40
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:47,666
@HOW_TO_FIGHT

41
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,625
[Shimura] Oh, now I understand.

42
00:02:50,375 --> 00:02:53,083
- I'm sorry.
- No. Don't be.

43
00:02:53,708 --> 00:02:57,791
You did all that for a stranger.
That's very considerate.

44
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:03,875
At any rate,

45
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,416
that's all the videos that exist.

46
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,375
- Huh?
- Yeah.

47
00:03:08,875 --> 00:03:11,041
I think you should reconsider

48
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,583
the medical fees exemption.

49
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:20,291
I must be going now.

50
00:03:21,625 --> 00:03:22,833
[Shimura] Wait, please.

51
00:03:26,916 --> 00:03:30,166
Will I… see you again?

52
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,208
Mm.

53
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:43,708
[door opens]

54
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:03,625
[tender music playing]

55
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,458
Sayonara.

56
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,125
- Are you okay, Mom?
- Mm-hmm.

57
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:21,583
[Shimura] Here we are.

58
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:23,666
There you go.

59
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,666
[mom] Phew!

60
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:27,916
- [Shimura] Okay.
- Thank you.

61
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,083
[nurse] Miss Asamiya.

62
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:31,833
Oh. Hello there.

63
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:34,333
Are you okay?
Are you looking for the director?

64
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:35,625
Uh, no.

65
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:39,583
Uh… do you know who that person is?

66
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:42,291
[nurse] Oh, that's Mrs. Shimura.

67
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:45,625
- He is such a good son.
- At least two miles!

68
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:47,833
[nurse] His mother is
in and out of hospital,

69
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:50,375
and he always takes
good care of her like that.

70
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:52,375
I'm Kaho Asamiya.

71
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,000
Nice to be working here!

72
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:56,416
If you have any questions,
just ask any of us.

73
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:58,916
[timer beeping]

74
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,125
Agh! Hot!

75
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,916
There it is! I found it!

76
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:17,541
Thank you!

77
00:05:22,416 --> 00:05:23,833
No way.

78
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:28,750
Asamiya!

79
00:05:40,958 --> 00:05:42,166
I'm home.

80
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,541
Where were you?

81
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:48,250
Nowhere special.

82
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,833
You went to see that guy, Kuwata.

83
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:54,791
I'm sorry.

84
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,833
I was worried about you.

85
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,583
I went into your room.

86
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,958
[gasps]

87
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:02,125
Keep out of my business.

88
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,291
What kind of parent
would I be if I didn't?

89
00:06:04,375 --> 00:06:06,416
When I can see that you're in pain.

90
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:09,083
This is our issue, nothing to do with you.

91
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:11,333
- You shouldn't interfere.
- No.

92
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:12,958
I'm responsible too.

93
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,416
I'm saying I'll help you.

94
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:43,041
I just wanted to say goodbye.

95
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,125
[poignant music playing]

96
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:54,458
[inaudible]

97
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:00,666
- [poignant music continues]
- [door opens]

98
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:03,708
[door closes]

99
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,666
BE STRONGER!
@VIRAL_HIT

100
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:11,333
You won't get
any more videos from TOU-KEI.

101
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:20,208
MMA MATCH

102
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:25,666
- [clicks]
- [crowd clamoring on video]

103
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,125
[suspenseful music playing]

104
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,750
[music fades]

105
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:03,958
[Eiji sighs]

106
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:07,416
So… have you made up your mind?

107
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:11,208
Mm. Yes, I have.

108
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,166
- I see.
- I'm going to the police.

109
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:17,291
Rumi…

110
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,291
Oh my God.

111
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:24,208
Tell me you're kidding me.

112
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,291
Or I'll talk to Mr. Kuwata himself.

113
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:28,666
[laughing]

114
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:35,166
Oh, yeah? You think
Mr. Kuwata doesn't know?

115
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:42,791
<i>He's the one who's giving the orders.</i>

116
00:08:45,541 --> 00:08:47,875
He likes to take advantage…

117
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:53,083
[laughs] …of weak…
and stupid people like you.

118
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,583
Hmm?

119
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:55,916
Well, then,

120
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,875
what if I go to the police?

121
00:08:58,958 --> 00:08:59,958
[sighs]

122
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:03,208
You know what'll happen
if you make an enemy out of him.

123
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:04,791
What?

124
00:09:07,041 --> 00:09:08,541
He'll make you disappear.

125
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,083
[Reo] <i>If he is…</i>

126
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:14,083
<i>you'd better protect him.</i>

127
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,458
He'll do what?

128
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:18,750
No, I just can't believe that.

129
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,333
[exhales]

130
00:09:21,416 --> 00:09:23,416
[ominous music playing]

131
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:25,791
Then…

132
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:30,291
why don't you see for yourself?

133
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:31,250
Huh?

134
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,458
<i>There was someone else</i>
<i>who tried to do the same thing as you.</i>

135
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:40,625
- [groans]
- [laughing]

136
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,458
[grunting]

137
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:50,333
Are you still alive? [laughs]

138
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:54,583
[grunting].

139
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,208
No, I'm against it.

140
00:10:05,291 --> 00:10:06,791
You should pull out.

141
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:12,208
The only reason you've won so far
is because the fight's had no rules.

142
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:16,166
Facing off with a trained fighter
in a ring is a different story.

143
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:20,125
Yeah, but I really need this money.

144
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:24,125
How many people do you think
will donate to you guys now?

145
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:27,875
Also, man, stop making her suffer.

146
00:10:27,958 --> 00:10:30,416
- Huh?
- Asamiya.

147
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:33,416
She doesn't want to have to keep
seeing you get hurt like this.

148
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,958
I'm afraid I can't help you with this one.

149
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,500
What am I supposed to do?

150
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:52,500
If there's no more videos…

151
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:55,208
[man] Hey, boy.

152
00:10:58,166 --> 00:10:59,833
Do you wanna see TOU-KEI?

153
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:00,791
Huh?

154
00:11:01,291 --> 00:11:05,833
[mimicking TOU-KEI] Hey my friends!
It's TOU-KEI here!

155
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:07,916
[quirky electronic music playing]

156
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:10,333
Huh? What?

157
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,041
[phone ringing]

158
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,166
Aki?

159
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:21,166
[Aki] <i>Come to my place right now</i>
<i>and bring Logan, who's there with you.</i>

160
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:25,083
[SHIMERUA] What the hell is going on?

161
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,458
Logan is an old friend of mine.

162
00:11:28,541 --> 00:11:30,625
He's been watching <i>Viral Hit</i>.

163
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:31,958
Okay, wait.

164
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:34,625
- TOU-KEI, you've known about him too.
- It's no big deal.

165
00:11:35,416 --> 00:11:36,750
I'm interested.

166
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:39,458
How did you get access to the vids?

167
00:11:40,458 --> 00:11:41,291
Oh.

168
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:46,625
The person who found this sent them to me.

169
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:48,791
This is mine.

170
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,125
You piss me off.

171
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:51,750
You gloomy-ass bitch.

172
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:55,708
You've had this the entire time?

173
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:57,333
So, then,

174
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,166
Mr. Logan, you're TOU-KEI, aren't you?

175
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,541
[chuckles] No.

176
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:02,458
Huh?

177
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:05,750
Then… who is TOU-KEI?

178
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,083
[man] It's me.

179
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:12,583
[tense music playing]

180
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:14,000
You're kidding!

181
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:16,458
Good to see you again, Master.

182
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,000
Master?

183
00:12:18,083 --> 00:12:21,750
Please don't call me that.
I don't deserve that title.

184
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:25,625
My father was a UFC fighter
in the American Association.

185
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:32,000
After I retired, I became Logan's coach.
And then he got injured during practice.

186
00:12:32,083 --> 00:12:34,166
He felt it was his fault.

187
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:37,208
So, he left the fighting world
and we moved back here.

188
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,750
But your body, it's, uh…

189
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,875
[grunts] It's shrunk a bit now, right?

190
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:44,000
Yoga will do that.

191
00:12:44,083 --> 00:12:45,125
Yoga?

192
00:12:45,208 --> 00:12:47,666
The secret
to Rickson and Gracie's strength,

193
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,583
I'll tell you now, it's yoga.

194
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:50,625
You should try it.

195
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:53,875
[laughs] Ah, I'll pass. Thank you.

196
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:58,000
Those videos…
they were made for Aki here.

197
00:12:58,916 --> 00:13:00,541
Made for Aki?

198
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,750
Mm.

199
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:05,791
You see Aki had
a difficult time adjusting to life abroad.

200
00:13:06,291 --> 00:13:10,291
- [chirping]
<i>- And her only friend… was a pet chicken.</i>

201
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,375
[young Aki crying]

202
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:16,833
[Aki's dad] <i>But, that chicken… he died.</i>

203
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:18,916
[tender music playing]2

204
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,750
BE STRONGER!

205
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:55,791
<i>Hello, guys! My name is TOU-KEI.</i>

206
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:59,708
<i>Why don't you come</i>
<i>and get stronger with me?</i>

207
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:04,166
At first, I made them to cheer Aki up,
but then I guess I started to get into it.

208
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,500
I was glad. It was good.

209
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:07,541
Huh?

210
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,291
I heard everything from Aki.

211
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:14,416
I swore to never get involved
in martial arts again.

212
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,833
But Aki chose you, son.

213
00:14:15,916 --> 00:14:18,041
Now I need to see
if you're worthy of my daughter--

214
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:20,250
- No, I think there's--
- There's not a lot of time.

215
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,583
We start right away.

216
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,125
- Let's get to it.
- Yeah.

217
00:14:25,625 --> 00:14:27,833
[dramatic brass music playing]

218
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:36,250
- Keep up!
- Yes, Sir.

219
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,166
- One, two! Come on!
- [Shimura grunts]

220
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:41,750
- One, two!
- [Shimura grunting]

221
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,041
- One, two! Ha!
- [Shimura] Ha!

222
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:44,291
[Aki's dad] One, two, hook.

223
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:48,208
- Come on, come on!
- [Shimura] Ready now. Jab! Jab!

224
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,666
- [Shimura grunting]
- Come on! Raise your elbow!

225
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:52,833
[groaning]

226
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:55,375
[Aki's dad] Come on, higher. Higher, yeah.

227
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:56,625
- [Shimura grunting]
- More!

228
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:59,375
Plant your feet, raise it. Plant! Raise!

229
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,458
Breath, breath, breath.

230
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:07,083
Breathe down into your belly now.
That's it. That's it.

231
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:10,250
- Good, good.  Now, higher!
- [Shimura grunting]

232
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:14,291
- And, roll!
- [Shimura grunting]

233
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:22,375
[choir vocalizing triumphantly]

234
00:15:28,291 --> 00:15:33,500
HIS FAMILY IS DIRT POOR LOL

235
00:15:34,791 --> 00:15:36,708
VIRAL HIT
ONSLAUGHT OF DEATH THREATS!!!

236
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,458
[straining]

237
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:44,666
[huffing]

238
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:50,875
[grunting]

239
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:57,416
- [Shimura grunting]
- [Aki's dad] Give me more!

240
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:00,708
[coughing]

241
00:16:00,791 --> 00:16:02,000
[yells] Ah!

242
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,375
[grunts]

243
00:16:03,458 --> 00:16:06,000
Yes! Very good! Come on, go again!

244
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:07,500
[straining]

245
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:11,416
[coughing]

246
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:16,291
[choir vocalizing triumphantly]

247
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:35,333
[Aki] You're ready!

248
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,791
[panting]

249
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,250
Ah! Ah!

250
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:46,583
You've done well to hold out this long.

251
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:51,541
Tomorrow will be the last day of training.

252
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:53,291
Can I…

253
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:55,500
Can I win with this?

254
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:58,166
Uh…

255
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:00,916
I'm sorry, but no.

256
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:04,083
You won't be able to win the game.

257
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,208
Huh?

258
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,333
[silent]

259
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:22,291
USING A CAMERA IS TIRING

260
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:23,875
YOU'RE MAKING A LADY WORK

261
00:17:29,125 --> 00:17:30,291
READ

262
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:32,666
[gentle music playing]

263
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:36,500
[Aki] <i>Hey, what are you doing?</i>

264
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:41,458
<i>You're the one who started </i>Viral Hit<i>.</i>

265
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:43,750
<i>What are we going to do without you?</i>

266
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:47,708
<i>Shimura is worried about you too.</i>

267
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,208
<i>Sheesh!</i>

268
00:17:52,791 --> 00:17:54,666
<i>You're making a girl work hard here.</i>

269
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,166
AKI YASHIO

270
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:00,833
[phone ringing]

271
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:10,083
[outgoing call ringing]

272
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:17,458
[ends call]

273
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:22,583
There you are!

274
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:29,833
<i>So things have gotten wild, you know.</i>

275
00:18:30,916 --> 00:18:35,458
The <i>Viral Hit </i>you created
has truly gone viral.

276
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,041
[voice breaking] Aki…

277
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,750
I'm sorry.

278
00:18:46,666 --> 00:18:47,541
I…

279
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:49,750
[Aki] <i>I preferred…</i>

280
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:54,791
<i>Viral Hit </i>with you a part of it.

281
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:04,458
You are a… great producer, you know?

282
00:19:06,666 --> 00:19:08,750
<i>We need you on the team.</i>

283
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,375
<i>Come back to us.</i>

284
00:19:16,166 --> 00:19:17,541
<i>We'll be waiting for you.</i>

285
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:32,875
[poignant music playing]

286
00:19:35,208 --> 00:19:38,916
VIRAL HIT BELONGS TO THE THREE OF US

287
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
[crying]

288
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:52,208
[sniffles]

289
00:19:56,875 --> 00:19:57,708
[sniffles]

290
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
[music fades]

291
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:17,625
[Shimura's mom] <i>Tomorrow is the big day.</i>

292
00:20:17,708 --> 00:20:18,708
Mm.

293
00:20:19,375 --> 00:20:20,958
- This is…
- Oh.

294
00:20:21,958 --> 00:20:24,416
Feels like
it's already getting a bit warm.

295
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:27,833
Maybe I can use it next year.

296
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:31,750
Mm. Okay, I'll wear it. Thanks.

297
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:38,166
I'm sorry.

298
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:43,000
I'm afraid this is all I can do for you.

299
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:47,041
Where's this coming from?

300
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,708
I wish I could find the ones
who are bad-mouthing you

301
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:53,333
and give them a piece of my mind.

302
00:20:55,583 --> 00:20:58,291
To tell them that you're
a really kindhearted kid.

303
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:02,625
You don't need to.

304
00:21:04,541 --> 00:21:07,500
If only I wasn't stuck in here like this.

305
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,333
I wish that you could do

306
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,791
the things you really want to.

307
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,333
You know, at first…

308
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:29,375
I was doing it for you.

309
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:32,458
- And then I think it changed.
- [gentle music playing]

310
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:33,666
And now…

311
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:37,333
there's more to it, really, you know.

312
00:21:39,708 --> 00:21:42,375
It made me realize
there's things I can do.

313
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:46,208
Even though I thought
I couldn't do anything.

314
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:50,291
I feel like I'm alive right now.

315
00:21:52,041 --> 00:21:53,333
I've never…

316
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:58,500
felt anything like this before.

317
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:02,666
And also,

318
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,708
I've made friends and it's great.

319
00:22:08,416 --> 00:22:10,625
To tell you the absolute truth,

320
00:22:11,125 --> 00:22:13,250
they're really quite annoying

321
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:15,458
and irritating.

322
00:22:16,875 --> 00:22:18,041
You know?

323
00:22:22,541 --> 00:22:23,416
And…

324
00:22:24,458 --> 00:22:26,958
I'm having the time of my life.

325
00:22:29,125 --> 00:22:31,083
You said to me…

326
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:35,041
that you're only young once.

327
00:22:38,083 --> 00:22:41,083
<i>Viral Hit</i>. This is my youth.

328
00:22:44,041 --> 00:22:48,291
I'll try my very best…
in this final match.

329
00:22:49,958 --> 00:22:51,041
So…

330
00:23:00,125 --> 00:23:01,208
So…

331
00:23:04,708 --> 00:23:06,833
Don't you give up either.

332
00:23:10,083 --> 00:23:13,208
I think you worry too much about me,
you know. [crying]

333
00:23:15,208 --> 00:23:17,416
I'm not gonna die so easily.

334
00:23:19,916 --> 00:23:20,750
[sniffles]

335
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:24,458
You should really be
worrying about yourself.

336
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:31,541
I don't want to see you get hit.

337
00:23:33,041 --> 00:23:35,500
Or see you hitting anybody else.

338
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:48,125
Don't you dare
even think about dying before me.

339
00:23:51,875 --> 00:23:52,833
[sniffling]

340
00:24:15,125 --> 00:24:17,125
[music fades]

341
00:24:22,791 --> 00:24:23,625
DOXXED

342
00:24:23,708 --> 00:24:26,541
HOT GIRLFRIEND'S DAD
RUNS URABE GENERAL HOSPITAL

343
00:24:30,541 --> 00:24:31,958
[boy 1] Oh, wow.

344
00:24:32,041 --> 00:24:35,250
- Isn't that… What?
- [boy 2] Wait, wait, wait.

345
00:24:35,333 --> 00:24:37,625
- [girl 1] Huh? Wow.
- [boy 1] Is that <i>Viral Hit</i>'s girlfriend?

346
00:24:37,708 --> 00:24:39,958
- [boy 2] The one that stages their shows?
- [boy 1] Yeah!

347
00:24:40,041 --> 00:24:42,625
[boy 2] Huh? She looks
nothing like the photos.

348
00:24:42,708 --> 00:24:45,708
- [girl 2] Hey, that girl.
- [girl 3] It's definitely her, right?

349
00:24:45,791 --> 00:24:46,875
[girl 3] It totally is.

350
00:24:46,958 --> 00:24:47,916
HER NAME IS KAHO ASAMIYA

351
00:24:48,375 --> 00:24:50,083
SHE'S A SENSELESS SPOILED BRAT

352
00:24:50,166 --> 00:24:51,583
SHE DESERVED THE ASSAULT

353
00:24:51,666 --> 00:24:53,666
[tense music playing]

354
00:24:57,208 --> 00:24:58,250
[gasps]

355
00:24:58,916 --> 00:25:00,916
[tense music continues]

356
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:05,583
[Kuwata] <i>These childish games</i>
<i>won't work forever.</i>

357
00:25:05,666 --> 00:25:08,208
[Toru] <i>This must be his doing.</i>
<i>Kuwata must be pulling the strings.</i>

358
00:25:08,291 --> 00:25:10,750
[Aki] <i>He saw Kuwata at the scene</i>
<i>where his friend died.</i>

359
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:13,291
[Ogi] <i>How many people</i>
<i>do you think will donate to you guys now?</i>

360
00:25:13,375 --> 00:25:15,125
[Kaho] <i>I think you should reconsider.</i>

361
00:25:15,208 --> 00:25:17,500
[Shimura's mom] <i>I don't want to see</i>
<i>you get hit.</i>

362
00:25:18,625 --> 00:25:21,166
<i>Or see you hitting anybody else.</i>

363
00:25:21,250 --> 00:25:24,208
<i>Don't you dare</i>
<i>even think about dying before me.</i>

364
00:25:41,333 --> 00:25:43,958
[music fades]

365
00:25:44,041 --> 00:25:46,458
[birds twittering]

366
00:25:53,583 --> 00:25:55,208
Okay, here we go.

367
00:25:57,708 --> 00:25:59,875
[zipping]

368
00:26:23,166 --> 00:26:25,166
[inaudible]

369
00:26:27,166 --> 00:26:29,166
[eerie music playing]

370
00:26:35,958 --> 00:26:37,041
[Kota gasps]

371
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:40,250
[no audible dialogue]

372
00:26:42,541 --> 00:26:43,916
[footsteps depart]

373
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,083
[door opens]

374
00:26:46,125 --> 00:26:47,208
[door closes]

375
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:08,500
[spectators clamoring]

376
00:27:14,416 --> 00:27:16,416
GIRLFRIEND HOPED TO
GET INTO MED SCHOOL!

377
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,750
[Shimura] Aki, tell me honestly.

378
00:27:17,833 --> 00:27:18,666
NOT FIT TO BE A DOC

379
00:27:19,166 --> 00:27:21,625
Do you think
what I've been doing is wrong?

380
00:27:22,708 --> 00:27:24,083
What are you saying?

381
00:27:25,791 --> 00:27:27,250
It's just that

382
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:30,750
friends who are
important to me have got hurt.

383
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:35,083
And I never set out to hurt anyone at all.

384
00:27:37,458 --> 00:27:39,458
[gentle music playing]

385
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:44,541
There's also

386
00:27:45,458 --> 00:27:47,708
other people who you have saved.

387
00:27:52,083 --> 00:27:53,791
And I think

388
00:27:54,291 --> 00:27:56,041
that I'm one of them.

389
00:27:59,541 --> 00:28:00,791
Without you…

390
00:28:03,291 --> 00:28:05,416
I would still be all alone.

391
00:28:12,625 --> 00:28:13,625
Shimura.

392
00:28:16,666 --> 00:28:18,125
To me, you're my

393
00:28:19,833 --> 00:28:21,500
one and only hero. [chuckles]

394
00:28:26,791 --> 00:28:27,833
That's nice.

395
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,416
[knocking]

396
00:28:32,625 --> 00:28:34,541
- It's time.
- Okay.

397
00:28:40,416 --> 00:28:42,083
Remember what I said.

398
00:28:42,583 --> 00:28:44,583
Shimura, you're not alone.

399
00:28:44,666 --> 00:28:47,833
TOU-KEI

400
00:28:56,708 --> 00:28:58,250
All right, let's go.

401
00:28:58,750 --> 00:29:01,625
Let's show them all what <i>Viral Hit </i>can do.

402
00:29:01,708 --> 00:29:03,500
You can count on it.

403
00:29:04,125 --> 00:29:05,750
I'll hit him real hard.

404
00:29:05,833 --> 00:29:08,375
Oh, yeah. You send him flying!

405
00:29:08,458 --> 00:29:10,458
[dramatic rock music playing]

406
00:29:12,958 --> 00:29:19,791
BAD FELLOWS

407
00:29:21,708 --> 00:29:27,083
[announcer] <i>Thank you for waiting.</i>
<i>We will now commence with the main event.</i>

408
00:29:27,166 --> 00:29:29,208
[crowd cheering]

409
00:29:29,291 --> 00:29:33,333
In the blue corner,
a local high school student

410
00:29:33,416 --> 00:29:37,625
<i>whose live stream fights</i>
<i>have taken the world by storm.</i>

411
00:29:38,125 --> 00:29:39,916
From <i>Viral Hit</i>…

412
00:29:40,791 --> 00:29:44,708
Kota Shimura!

413
00:29:44,791 --> 00:29:47,500
[crowd clamoring, jeering]

414
00:29:56,333 --> 00:29:58,541
[jeering continues]

415
00:29:58,625 --> 00:30:00,916
[crowd booing]

416
00:30:18,125 --> 00:30:19,666
[Ogi] This is totally an away game.

417
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,500
[Aki's dad] All right.

418
00:30:25,166 --> 00:30:26,583
<i>Do your best.</i>

419
00:30:26,666 --> 00:30:28,666
[dramatic rock music continues]

420
00:30:34,583 --> 00:30:37,750
KUWATA 172,300 YEN VS SHIMURA 300 YEN

421
00:30:40,583 --> 00:30:43,208
[announcer] Next, in the red corner,

422
00:30:44,291 --> 00:30:46,958
<i>BAD FELLOWS </i>creator and owner…

423
00:30:47,041 --> 00:30:48,375
[crowd clamoring]

424
00:30:48,458 --> 00:30:52,166
…and a revolutionary
in the world of martial arts,

425
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:55,125
<i>Yugo Kuwata!</i>

426
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:58,166
- [man 1] Go Kuwata!
- [man 2] You're the best, Kuwata!

427
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:01,625
- [crowd cheering, whooping]
- [hip-hop music playing]

428
00:31:03,666 --> 00:31:06,291
[man 3] Kuwata! Kuwata!

429
00:31:10,291 --> 00:31:12,125
[man 4] Let's go, Kuwata!

430
00:31:12,208 --> 00:31:14,583
[girls screaming]

431
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:16,250
Yeah, Kuwata.

432
00:31:38,333 --> 00:31:39,416
[referee] Center!

433
00:31:44,166 --> 00:31:46,291
Three rounds. No headbutting.

434
00:31:46,375 --> 00:31:49,000
Hitting the back of the head,
spine strikes, groin strikes,

435
00:31:49,083 --> 00:31:50,708
biting, or eye-gouging.

436
00:31:51,291 --> 00:31:52,291
Touch gloves.

437
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:58,666
What do you say?
Gonna make a lot of money today?

438
00:32:01,041 --> 00:32:02,500
<i>I'm sure they're all dying to see it.</i>

439
00:32:02,583 --> 00:32:03,458
KUWATA VS SHIMURA

440
00:32:04,208 --> 00:32:08,000
<i>They want to see you, the villain,</i>
<i>get beaten and humiliated.</i>

441
00:32:09,125 --> 00:32:11,750
<i>You're the one who's gonna get beaten.</i>

442
00:32:13,166 --> 00:32:15,791
Okay. Back to your corners.

443
00:32:18,208 --> 00:32:20,458
[crowd roaring on live stream]

444
00:32:24,041 --> 00:32:25,833
[announcer] Round one!

445
00:32:25,916 --> 00:32:27,125
- Fight.
- [dings]

446
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,500
[crowd roaring]

447
00:32:33,916 --> 00:32:35,458
[man 5] <i>Go, Kuwata.</i>

448
00:32:37,541 --> 00:32:38,416
[Shimura grunts]

449
00:32:44,125 --> 00:32:46,250
[crowd cheering, whooping]

450
00:32:48,791 --> 00:32:50,375
[both grunting]

451
00:32:51,833 --> 00:32:54,958
What's the matter, huh?
You haven't landed a single punch.

452
00:32:59,375 --> 00:33:01,500
[both grunting]

453
00:33:04,416 --> 00:33:06,125
[man 6] <i>Beat him down, Kuwata!</i>

454
00:33:06,208 --> 00:33:08,250
[crowd clamoring]

455
00:33:08,333 --> 00:33:11,375
You won't make any money
if the game ends in the first round.

456
00:33:12,708 --> 00:33:14,125
Yeah, you better get up.

457
00:33:18,916 --> 00:33:19,875
SHIMURA 300YEN

458
00:33:19,958 --> 00:33:21,458
[Aki] It's not good.

459
00:33:29,750 --> 00:33:30,916
START LIVE STREAM

460
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:31,875
[beeps]

461
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:39,208
<i>Hello everyone.</i>

462
00:33:39,291 --> 00:33:40,750
IS IT REALLY HER?
HE'S FIGHTING NOW!

463
00:33:40,833 --> 00:33:44,833
I'm the one causing
the stir on social media.

464
00:33:47,416 --> 00:33:49,333
I'm <i>Viral Hit'</i>s girlfriend.

465
00:33:49,416 --> 00:33:52,416
VIRAL HIT'S GIRLFRIEND IS LIVE!

466
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:55,000
[crowd clamoring on live stream]

467
00:33:55,083 --> 00:33:56,541
<i>I've now seen…</i>

468
00:33:58,541 --> 00:34:02,791
<i>many comments bashing Shimura,</i>
<i>saying he's making money out of violence.</i>

469
00:34:03,916 --> 00:34:04,916
It's true.

470
00:34:06,208 --> 00:34:09,000
We shouldn't ever justify
acts of violence.

471
00:34:10,250 --> 00:34:11,083
<i>But…</i>

472
00:34:13,166 --> 00:34:15,500
I'm partially the one you should accuse…

473
00:34:17,208 --> 00:34:18,916
of turning him to violence.

474
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:21,000
[poignant music playing]

475
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:23,416
I have lived

476
00:34:24,250 --> 00:34:25,958
my life in shackles

477
00:34:26,541 --> 00:34:29,250
<i>doing whatever my parents instructed.</i>

478
00:34:29,791 --> 00:34:32,166
<i>At some point,</i>
<i>I had stopped fighting back.</i>

479
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:35,208
I thought it was somewhat easier this way.

480
00:34:37,291 --> 00:34:39,625
To stay weak rather than resist.

481
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,416
<i>Facing reality and fighting back</i>

482
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,791
<i>takes a lot of courage.</i>

483
00:34:47,708 --> 00:34:49,791
<i>It's not easy to accomplish.</i>

484
00:34:51,291 --> 00:34:53,125
I started to see

485
00:34:53,625 --> 00:34:55,250
myself in Shimura's image.

486
00:34:56,458 --> 00:34:58,375
When Shimura fought,

487
00:34:59,333 --> 00:35:02,000
I felt like I'd also become stronger.

488
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:05,375
Surely…

489
00:35:05,458 --> 00:35:06,458
HE GAVE ME COURAGE

490
00:35:06,541 --> 00:35:07,541
TRUE

491
00:35:07,625 --> 00:35:09,833
<i>…I wasn't the only one.</i>

492
00:35:09,916 --> 00:35:11,083
I'M TEARING UP

493
00:35:11,166 --> 00:35:12,750
MY HEART IS POUNDING

494
00:35:12,833 --> 00:35:14,750
Shimura is strong.

495
00:35:17,958 --> 00:35:19,875
He made a choice to protect another.

496
00:35:21,958 --> 00:35:24,500
The only way he could change his reality,

497
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:29,625
was by raising both his fists high.

498
00:35:36,166 --> 00:35:39,125
<i>If you're going to criticize Shimura</i>
<i>for these acts…</i>

499
00:35:39,250 --> 00:35:40,333
I MISUNDERSTOOD HIM

500
00:35:40,416 --> 00:35:44,875
<i>…then what about the justice</i>
<i>you demand hiding behind screens.</i>

501
00:35:45,541 --> 00:35:47,916
<i>You make accusations</i>
<i>and you gang up on him</i>

502
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,500
when you think it's okay.

503
00:35:50,583 --> 00:35:52,083
I think your justice…

504
00:35:54,166 --> 00:35:56,291
is the worst type of violence.

505
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:03,041
I won't run or hide anymore.

506
00:36:04,750 --> 00:36:05,875
That's why

507
00:36:07,291 --> 00:36:09,833
I chose to talk to you all here like this.

508
00:36:11,750 --> 00:36:14,375
<i>To fight against invisible violence.</i>

509
00:36:22,208 --> 00:36:24,250
[crowd cheering]

510
00:36:24,791 --> 00:36:26,000
[both grunting]

511
00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:27,416
[punch echoes]

512
00:36:31,458 --> 00:36:32,708
[crowd cheering]

513
00:36:32,791 --> 00:36:33,625
[dings]

514
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:35,875
[Shimura exhales]

515
00:36:39,208 --> 00:36:40,541
[groaning]

516
00:36:44,791 --> 00:36:46,375
[crowd clamoring]

517
00:36:48,666 --> 00:36:49,541
Thanks.

518
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,166
Shimura. Look at this.

519
00:36:56,916 --> 00:36:58,875
Donations are starting to pour in.

520
00:36:58,958 --> 00:36:59,833
What?

521
00:37:00,791 --> 00:37:02,000
It's Asamiya! What's she doing?

522
00:37:02,083 --> 00:37:03,333
YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S STORY MOVED ME

523
00:37:03,416 --> 00:37:04,541
[Toru] Let me go!

524
00:37:04,625 --> 00:37:05,750
Let go of me!

525
00:37:05,833 --> 00:37:07,500
Hey! Take your hands off!

526
00:37:07,583 --> 00:37:09,875
- Kaneko!
- Hey, Shimura!

527
00:37:13,250 --> 00:37:15,333
- Sorry, I'm late.
- What happened to your face?

528
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:19,791
Some punks hassled me on the way.
Don't worry about it.

529
00:37:20,291 --> 00:37:23,250
How's it going?
My counterpunch did the trick, didn't it?

530
00:37:23,333 --> 00:37:25,291
YOUR GIRLFRIEND IS ROOTING FOR YOU

531
00:37:26,166 --> 00:37:27,333
[gasps]

532
00:37:30,750 --> 00:37:33,791
Hey, <i>Viral Hit</i>'s girlfriend,
I need a favor.

533
00:37:33,875 --> 00:37:35,166
Was this your doing?

534
00:37:35,250 --> 00:37:39,375
I guess so. And there's…
more than one punch to come.

535
00:37:40,958 --> 00:37:42,583
Right now, she's causing a stir.

536
00:37:44,375 --> 00:37:46,541
KOTA SHIMURA 145,900 YEN

537
00:37:46,625 --> 00:37:47,500
[sighs]

538
00:37:47,583 --> 00:37:49,458
[clears throat] Asshole!

539
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:53,875
Rumi.

540
00:37:54,583 --> 00:37:55,958
What the hell are you doing here?

541
00:37:56,041 --> 00:37:58,208
I thought that I should come
and let you know.

542
00:37:58,291 --> 00:38:01,416
[Eiji] <i>You know what'll happen</i>
<i>if you make an enemy of him.</i>

543
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:02,500
[Rumi] <i>What?</i>

544
00:38:02,583 --> 00:38:04,208
[Eiji] <i>He'll make you disappear.</i>

545
00:38:04,291 --> 00:38:07,791
[Rumi] <i>I heard he's killed</i>
<i>a person before.</i>

546
00:38:07,875 --> 00:38:09,166
What the hell have you done?

547
00:38:09,833 --> 00:38:11,125
[Rumi] <i>Is it true?</i>

548
00:38:12,250 --> 00:38:15,250
<i>He and a group of men,</i>
<i>they beat a boy to death.</i>

549
00:38:15,333 --> 00:38:16,458
[huffs]

550
00:38:16,541 --> 00:38:18,666
<i>It wasn't a group of men.</i>

551
00:38:19,250 --> 00:38:20,583
<i>It was Kuwata.</i>

552
00:38:21,083 --> 00:38:24,541
<i>- Kuwata killed him alone.</i>
- [gasps] Wow!

553
00:38:24,625 --> 00:38:27,000
I just posted it.
It's already got 10,000 likes.

554
00:38:27,083 --> 00:38:29,833
- Bitch. You understand what you've done?
- [Rumi] Hey.

555
00:38:30,708 --> 00:38:32,875
Maybe you're gonna be the one

556
00:38:33,750 --> 00:38:35,250
that'll disappear.

557
00:38:37,958 --> 00:38:38,958
[gasps]

558
00:38:39,958 --> 00:38:41,958
[spluttering]

559
00:38:42,458 --> 00:38:43,916
[crying]

560
00:38:47,041 --> 00:38:49,291
It's <i>Viral Hit</i>'s time now.

561
00:38:50,750 --> 00:38:52,000
[women scream]

562
00:38:53,250 --> 00:38:54,083
[gasps]

563
00:38:56,166 --> 00:38:57,333
Good work.

564
00:38:58,291 --> 00:39:00,208
- [crowd clamoring]
- [Toru] Shimura.

565
00:39:00,291 --> 00:39:02,125
There's nothing to worry about now.

566
00:39:02,208 --> 00:39:03,541
[tense music playing]

567
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:05,125
You're not the only one.

568
00:39:05,208 --> 00:39:07,041
You're not alone there in the ring.

569
00:39:08,458 --> 00:39:09,375
We're all here

570
00:39:09,958 --> 00:39:11,625
fighting alongside you.

571
00:39:13,083 --> 00:39:14,250
Go knock him out!

572
00:39:15,333 --> 00:39:18,041
All right.
We'll use our trick in this round.

573
00:39:26,625 --> 00:39:28,750
Seconds out, please. Seconds out.

574
00:39:30,416 --> 00:39:32,291
<i>Round two!</i>

575
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:34,291
- [dings]
- Fight! Go Shimura!

576
00:39:38,333 --> 00:39:39,250
Yeah!

577
00:39:41,416 --> 00:39:43,458
[Aki] The donations are skyrocketing!

578
00:39:43,541 --> 00:39:45,125
How did you make this happen?

579
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:49,791
I told you. I'm a great producer, you see?

580
00:39:49,875 --> 00:39:52,291
[all chattering]

581
00:39:53,916 --> 00:39:54,791
Yeah!

582
00:39:54,875 --> 00:39:57,000
[both grunting]

583
00:40:00,333 --> 00:40:01,333
[grunts]

584
00:40:05,041 --> 00:40:05,916
What's wrong?

585
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:08,583
Huh? What was it you did? What?

586
00:40:08,666 --> 00:40:10,291
- Vegetable oil.
- [Toru] What?

587
00:40:10,375 --> 00:40:12,083
What a dirty trick.

588
00:40:12,708 --> 00:40:15,375
It's a fight. Isn't it?

589
00:40:16,833 --> 00:40:17,958
[grunts]

590
00:40:18,041 --> 00:40:19,416
I need your strength.

591
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:21,125
[tense music continues]

592
00:40:21,208 --> 00:40:25,875
Oh, and… please, everyone support Shimura.

593
00:40:25,958 --> 00:40:27,833
- What are you doing?!
- [crying]

594
00:40:27,916 --> 00:40:29,333
- Give it to me!
- No, stop it!

595
00:40:29,416 --> 00:40:30,750
Give… give it!

596
00:40:31,333 --> 00:40:34,083
How much more will you humiliate me
before you're satisfied?

597
00:40:34,166 --> 00:40:35,291
Leave me alone!

598
00:40:36,083 --> 00:40:39,666
Do you… even understand what you're doing?

599
00:40:41,166 --> 00:40:43,166
Now, this is why you're such a failure!

600
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:44,666
I've had enough!

601
00:40:45,458 --> 00:40:46,750
[music fades]

602
00:40:46,833 --> 00:40:49,416
[Shimura roaring]

603
00:40:52,416 --> 00:40:54,208
- [tense music resumes]
- [crowd roaring]

604
00:40:56,625 --> 00:40:59,375
[Shimura] <i>Fighting mindset,</i>
<i>rule number one.</i>

605
00:40:59,458 --> 00:41:01,250
<i>Don't lost your cool. </i>

606
00:41:02,666 --> 00:41:05,125
You little asshole.

607
00:41:05,208 --> 00:41:07,625
[approaching motorcycle revving]

608
00:41:10,875 --> 00:41:12,750
- Get on.
- Tatsuya.

609
00:41:12,833 --> 00:41:15,208
[fighters grunting]

610
00:41:18,166 --> 00:41:20,875
[Toru] Run. Run!  Come on! Get up!

611
00:41:20,958 --> 00:41:22,708
[Aki] Shimura, go!

612
00:41:22,791 --> 00:41:25,083
[suspenseful music playing]

613
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:29,041
[fighters continue grunting]

614
00:41:29,125 --> 00:41:31,708
This is bad.
That one punch, it made him angry.

615
00:41:35,250 --> 00:41:36,375
Guard. Guard!

616
00:41:40,541 --> 00:41:41,958
[crying]

617
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:53,291
[crowd clamoring, booing]

618
00:41:53,375 --> 00:41:55,291
[shakily] Shimura! Shimura!

619
00:41:55,375 --> 00:41:57,375
[referee] And down! Back to your corner!

620
00:41:57,458 --> 00:42:00,125
- How much have we made so far?
- Only about two million.

621
00:42:00,208 --> 00:42:01,750
- [crowd] Three! Four!
- Shimura! Get up!

622
00:42:01,833 --> 00:42:03,250
- You can't be done!
- [crowd] Five!

623
00:42:03,333 --> 00:42:08,291
- [Toru] Get up, Shimura!
- [crowd] Six! Seven! Eight! Nine!

624
00:42:08,375 --> 00:42:10,916
You okay? You're good? All right!

625
00:42:11,541 --> 00:42:12,750
- [dings]
- [referee] Stop!

626
00:42:12,833 --> 00:42:16,708
[crowd clamoring, booing]

627
00:42:20,500 --> 00:42:21,500
Come here.

628
00:42:25,416 --> 00:42:26,708
Saved by the bell.

629
00:42:30,833 --> 00:42:32,291
[gasping] What did we make?

630
00:42:32,375 --> 00:42:33,791
Only around two million.

631
00:42:34,666 --> 00:42:36,916
I see. That's not enough.

632
00:42:37,416 --> 00:42:40,333
Shimura, this next round is the last.

633
00:42:40,416 --> 00:42:41,416
Hang on till the end.

634
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,166
I know, I know.

635
00:42:43,250 --> 00:42:45,875
Show them what <i>Viral Hit'</i>s made of.
You can do this!

636
00:42:46,916 --> 00:42:50,041
[announcer] Seconds out.
Seconds out, please.

637
00:42:50,125 --> 00:42:51,458
<i>Your mom's watching.</i>

638
00:42:54,916 --> 00:42:55,833
[sniffs]

639
00:42:55,916 --> 00:42:57,041
[exhales]

640
00:42:57,125 --> 00:42:59,083
[suspenseful music playing]

641
00:43:04,083 --> 00:43:06,333
[announcer] Final round!

642
00:43:06,416 --> 00:43:07,416
- Fight!
- [dings]

643
00:43:09,125 --> 00:43:10,541
[fighters grunting]

644
00:43:22,125 --> 00:43:24,583
That's good! Keep going like that!

645
00:43:27,083 --> 00:43:28,333
Go Shimura!

646
00:43:30,833 --> 00:43:31,833
[music stops]

647
00:43:32,833 --> 00:43:35,750
What are you doing?!
Think about your training!

648
00:43:35,833 --> 00:43:37,833
[suspenseful music resumes]

649
00:44:04,083 --> 00:44:05,708
[music intensifies]

650
00:44:10,458 --> 00:44:11,791
[both gasps]

651
00:44:14,625 --> 00:44:16,625
- Yes, Shimura!
- Go, now! Go!

652
00:44:16,708 --> 00:44:17,583
[gasps]

653
00:44:18,291 --> 00:44:21,125
[revving]

654
00:44:24,875 --> 00:44:26,583
- Thank you, Tatsuya.
- Go quickly.

655
00:44:26,666 --> 00:44:27,625
[grunts]

656
00:44:38,291 --> 00:44:40,750
- [cracking]
- [Shimura screams]

657
00:44:40,833 --> 00:44:42,625
[Shimura yelping]

658
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:52,625
[music fades]

659
00:45:14,750 --> 00:45:16,458
[crowd clamoring]

660
00:45:16,541 --> 00:45:17,375
Shimura!

661
00:45:17,458 --> 00:45:19,583
- Down! Neutral!
- [announcer] Down!

662
00:45:20,208 --> 00:45:22,416
[referee and announcer] One! Two!

663
00:45:23,208 --> 00:45:24,208
This is bad.

664
00:45:25,041 --> 00:45:26,000
[announcer] Three…

665
00:45:26,083 --> 00:45:27,416
Hang in there.

666
00:45:27,500 --> 00:45:29,500
- [muffled] Get up!
- Get up, Shimura!

667
00:45:29,583 --> 00:45:32,666
[echoing] Get up!

668
00:45:53,708 --> 00:45:56,208
[dreamy music playing]

669
00:46:11,791 --> 00:46:14,291
HEY, GET UP

670
00:46:14,375 --> 00:46:16,833
PLEASE GET UP

671
00:46:19,833 --> 00:46:21,791
IT'S NOT THE END YET

672
00:46:21,875 --> 00:46:24,083
I NEED YOU TO GET UP!

673
00:46:47,041 --> 00:46:48,541
YOU GAVE US COURAGE

674
00:46:48,625 --> 00:46:50,708
NOW IT'S OUR TURN TO HELP YOU

675
00:46:52,625 --> 00:46:54,166
WE'LL NEVER ABANDON YOU

676
00:46:54,250 --> 00:46:56,625
WE'RE YOUR FRIENDS TOO

677
00:47:01,375 --> 00:47:03,750
LET US DREAM ONE MORE TIME

678
00:47:03,833 --> 00:47:06,333
[music fades]

679
00:47:07,541 --> 00:47:09,916
[suspenseful music playing]

680
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,833
- [Aki] Shimura! Get up!
- [crowd clamoring]

681
00:47:11,916 --> 00:47:13,916
[Toru] Get up!

682
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:16,375
- Get up, Shimura! Stand up!
- [Toru] Yes!

683
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:18,083
[gasping]

684
00:47:19,458 --> 00:47:20,333
Seven!

685
00:47:21,416 --> 00:47:24,666
[all cheering]

686
00:47:24,750 --> 00:47:26,291
- Eight!
- [Shimura gasping]

687
00:47:26,375 --> 00:47:28,125
- [crowd cheering]
- Nine!

688
00:47:28,208 --> 00:47:29,250
[referee] You okay?

689
00:47:31,333 --> 00:47:33,416
[rock music playing]

690
00:47:34,125 --> 00:47:35,333
Shimura!

691
00:47:36,416 --> 00:47:38,958
Donations are pouring in like crazy.

692
00:47:39,041 --> 00:47:42,833
Shimura! Not much longer!
Hang in there till the end!

693
00:47:42,916 --> 00:47:44,083
[referee] Can you do it?

694
00:47:45,958 --> 00:47:46,791
Fight!

695
00:47:50,666 --> 00:47:51,541
[grunting]

696
00:47:53,208 --> 00:47:55,833
- [growls]
- [groaning]

697
00:48:02,291 --> 00:48:03,541
[bell dings]

698
00:48:04,375 --> 00:48:05,541
I'm sorry, but no.

699
00:48:07,375 --> 00:48:09,250
You won't be able to win the game.

700
00:48:14,916 --> 00:48:16,458
But I only mean the game.

701
00:48:18,375 --> 00:48:20,208
So he can still beat Kuwata?

702
00:48:20,291 --> 00:48:21,791
In a fight, yes.

703
00:48:21,875 --> 00:48:24,000
[rock music playing]

704
00:48:42,916 --> 00:48:44,833
[roaring] Ya!

705
00:48:46,916 --> 00:48:49,000
- [dinging]
- [referee] Stop! He's down!

706
00:48:51,708 --> 00:48:57,833
[announcer] Due to Shimura's foul,
the winner of the match is Yugo Kuwata!

707
00:48:57,916 --> 00:49:00,083
[rock music fanfare playing]

708
00:49:00,166 --> 00:49:02,791
[crowd clamoring]

709
00:49:08,458 --> 00:49:09,291
IT'S A MIRACLE

710
00:49:11,291 --> 00:49:12,166
[inaudible]

711
00:49:16,333 --> 00:49:17,875
Well done!

712
00:49:18,458 --> 00:49:21,916
You really are the best streamer ever!

713
00:49:24,833 --> 00:49:27,000
[gasping]

714
00:49:27,083 --> 00:49:29,750
[both squealing]

715
00:49:29,833 --> 00:49:31,500
[music subsides]

716
00:49:31,583 --> 00:49:32,416
You pass.

717
00:49:32,500 --> 00:49:34,583
[poignant music playing]

718
00:49:38,416 --> 00:49:39,416
[crying]

719
00:49:40,916 --> 00:49:43,000
[crying]

720
00:49:52,333 --> 00:49:53,208
How much?

721
00:49:54,291 --> 00:49:55,791
What did we earn?

722
00:49:56,375 --> 00:49:59,041
[Japanese rock music playing]

723
00:50:08,208 --> 00:50:15,208
VIRAL HIT

724
00:50:20,416 --> 00:50:22,333
[Japanese rock music continues]

725
00:51:31,833 --> 00:51:32,833
[music ends]
